I need to identify the line items that represent amounts owed by the entity for goods or services received or purchased on credit.

Looking at the balance sheet, this type of liability is typically recorded as "Accounts Payable." Accounts Payable represents the money a company owes to its suppliers or vendors for goods or services purchased on credit.

In the balance sheet provided:
- The "Accounts Payable" had an initial amount of 0.00 on 2023-12-31
- The "Accounts Payable" had an end amount of 1240000.00 on 2024-01-29

Therefore, the amounts owed by the entity for goods or services received or purchased on credit are:
- Initial value: 0.00
- End value: 1240000.00
